EDIT: wait, you‚Äôre running solenoids off of PWM? They should be run from the PCM or the relay ports, unless you‚Äôre driving them with a motor controller which is pretty strange (overkill).
_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _

From here down, assuming that you‚Äôre driving a motor controller from PWM.

You‚Äôd have to write a driver, and it wouldn‚Äôt be legal.

Are you using the PWMs which are part of the MXP connector? There are eight more there.

Looking at the pinout (figure 4 here), most if not all of the PWM ports are next to a ground, so you won‚Äôt need a full breakout, just a cable with a three-port housing at one end with male pins at either end for the motor controller, and two female pins at the other for the MXP. One black and one preferably white or yellow wire.

  1. Add a second PCM.
  2. Use the new REV Pnematic Hub that has 16 channels.
